---
import BackToTop from "@components/ui/BackToTop.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main>
    <article class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      <div
        class="bg-white dark:bg-black rounded-lg shadow-lg overflow-hidden max-w-4xl mx-auto border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
      >
        <!-- Article Header -->
        <div class="p-8 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-black dark:text-white">
            From Cypress to Playwright - Saleor's Voyage
          </h1>
          <div
            class="flex items-center text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm"
          >
            <span>Published on DEV.to</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Article Content -->
        <div class="p-8">
          <div class="text-black dark:text-white space-y-6">
            <p class="text-xl">
              This is the story of Saleor's path from our early days of
              automated testing, to adapting to new tools, and finally to where
              we stand today with a more robust and efficient testing framework.
            </p>

            <p>
              Saleor recently migrated our end-to-end test suite from Cypress to
              Playwright. In this article we share our journey, the challenges
              we encountered, and how the transition unfolded.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8">How it started</h2>
            <p>
              Let's take a trip back to 2020. It's the beginning of the pandemic
              and I'm diving into adding the first storefront end-to-end tests
              written in Cypress. Back then, we didn't have a CI/CD setup -
              GitHub history shows that our deployment workflow was established
              in 2021.
            </p>

            <div
              class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700"
            >
              <a
                href="https://dev.to/saleor/from-cypress-to-playwright-saleors-voyage-5d8f"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-orange-600 dark:text-orange hover:underline"
              >
                Read the full article on DEV.to
                <svg
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  class="h-4 w-4 ml-1"
                  viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                  fill="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    fill-rule="evenodd"
                    d="M10.293 3.293a1 1 0 011.414 0l6 6a1 1 0 010 1.414l-6 6a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L14.586 11H3a1 1 0 110-2h11.586l-4.293-4.293a1 1 0 010-1.414z"
                    clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
    <BackToTop />
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .lead-paragraph {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #4a5568;
  }

  :global(.dark) .lead-paragraph {
    color: #e2e8f0;
  }

  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }

  .prose h1,
  .prose h2 {
    color: inherit;
  }
</style>
